{"lemma":"فَتّاح","slug":"فَتّاح","root":"ف.ت.ح","root_slug":"ف-ت-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَتّاح","root":"فتح","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32888"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AD"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"opener (of the gates of profit and sustenance: an attribute of God)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conqueror"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Occupational noun from the root ف ت ح (f t ḥ), associated with فَتَحَ (fataḥa, “to open, conquer”)."},"ipa":["/fat.taːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32888","headword_ar":"فَتَّاحٌ","root":"ftH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An opener:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unlocker."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A conquerer."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-  And], in the dial. of Himyer, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A judge; one who decides between litigants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA:) it is like ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtiHN","text_ar":"فَاتِحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but [this signifies simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judging,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the former] has an intensive signification. (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfat~aAHu","text_ar":"الفَتَّاحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an epithet applied to God, in the Kur xxxiv. 25, means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Judge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to IAth, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Opener of the gates of sustenance and of mercy to his servants."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotN fat~aAHN","text_ar":"بَيْتٌ فَتَّاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ample, house"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Fáïk, TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfat~aAHu","text_ar":"الفَتَّاحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is black, and which moves about its tail much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often; white in the base of the tail, beneath it; and there is a sort thereof red;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u EajolaAna","text_ar":"اُمُّ عَجْلَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ejl","text_ar":"عجل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataAtiyHu","text_ar":"فَتَاتِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) to which is added in the K, “ without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ” but there is no reason why it should not have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to it; and perhaps it should be correctly “ without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", ” i. e. it is not pluralized with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as an affix to the sing.], as in the L &c. (MF, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}